title: Unemployment rate in South Korea 2024
summary: This is a line chart with an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Unemployment rate, containing a total of 11 data points.
Overall Unemployment rate has increased over the Year.

Unemployment rate is roughly increasing from 2014 to 2015, roughly constant from 2015 to 2017, gradually increasing from 2017 to 2020, roughly constant from 2020 to 2021, and lastly slightly decreasing from 2021 to 2024.
The steepest increase occurs in between the Year 2018 and 2019.
The highest Unemployment rate, of value 4.15 was reached at Year 2020
The lowest Unemployment rate, of value 3.49 was reported at Year 2014
